CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 3, 1963, pg. 1, reads: "Will Demonstrations Be Staged Here? - Members of Pittsburgh's newly formed Unity Committee have selected several targets around Pittsburgh as sites of possible mass demonstrations. Four of them are shown here.  Left to right: Equitable Gas Co. on the Boulevard of the Allies... - Harris Photos
TitMainTitle: Equitable Gas Company building, 420 Boulevard of the Allies, Downtown
